---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="Metric vs Imperial — Quick Reference Guide for Everyday Conversions" description="A complete quick reference for metric and imperial conversions. Weight, length, volume, temperature — all the common conversions in one place. Free, no sign-up." keywords="metric vs imperial, metric to imperial conversion, kg to lbs, cm to inches, litres to gallons, celsius to fahrenheit, unit conversion guide, measurement systems">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Metric vs Imperial — Quick Reference Guide for Everyday Conversions",
    "description": "A complete quick reference for metric and imperial conversions. Weight, length, volume, temperature in one place.",
    "datePublished": "2025-06-25",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "xConvert24.com", "url": "https://www.xconvert24.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "xConvert24.com", "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.xconvert24.com/web-app-manifest-512x512.png" } },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.xconvert24.com/blog/metric-vs-imperial-quick-reference" }
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Reference</span>
      </nav>

      <BlogCrossLinks title="Metric vs Imperial — Quick Reference Guide for Everyday Conversions" />

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2025-06-25">June 25, 2025</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Whether you are reading a recipe from America, buying furniture from a European website, or checking the weather forecast in a different country, you will encounter both metric and imperial measurements. This quick reference gives you the conversions you need most often — plus links to our free converters for exact calculations.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Two Systems at a Glance</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/10">
          <p class="text-blue-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📐 Metric (SI)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Used by 95% of the world. Base-10 system. Metres, kilograms, litres, Celsius. Simple to scale (multiply/divide by 10, 100, 1000).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📏 Imperial/US Customary</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Used primarily in the US, Liberia, Myanmar. Feet, pounds, gallons, Fahrenheit. Irregular scaling (12 inches = 1 foot, 3 feet = 1 yard).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">The metric system was formalised during the French Revolution and has since been adopted by virtually every country. The imperial system evolved from older English units and persists primarily in the United States for everyday use, though even American science and medicine use metric. This means cross-system conversion is a daily necessity for international communication.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Weight Conversions</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Metric</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Imperial</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Quick Rule</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 kg</td><td class="px-4 py-3">2.205 lbs</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Double and add 10%</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 gram</td><td class="px-4 py-3">0.035 oz</td><td class="px-4 py-3">28g ≈ 1 oz</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 tonne</td><td class="px-4 py-3">2,205 lbs</td><td class="px-4 py-3">≈ 1.1 US tons</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 stone</td><td class="px-4 py-3">14 lbs / 6.35 kg</td><td class="px-4 py-3">UK body weight unit</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">The most common conversion people search for is kilograms to pounds — whether for luggage limits, body weight, or recipe scaling. Our <a href="/convert/weight" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 hover:underline font-medium">Weight Converter</a> handles all these instantly.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Length Conversions</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Metric</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Imperial</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Quick Rule</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 cm</td><td class="px-4 py-3">0.394 inches</td><td class="px-4 py-3">2.54 cm = 1 inch</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 metre</td><td class="px-4 py-3">3.281 feet</td><td class="px-4 py-3">≈ 3 ft 3 in</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 km</td><td class="px-4 py-3">0.621 miles</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Multiply km by 0.6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 mile</td><td class="px-4 py-3">1.609 km</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Multiply miles by 1.6</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">6 ft</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">= 183 cm</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">5'7"</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">= 170 cm</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">100 km</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">= 62 miles</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">1 marathon</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">= 42.2 km / 26.2 mi</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/how-tall-is-6-feet-in-cm/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">How Tall is 6 Feet in CM? — height conversion explained</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/driving-distances-km-vs-miles/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Driving Distances: KM vs Miles — when precision matters</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Volume Conversions</h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Metric</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Imperial</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Notes</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 litre</td><td class="px-4 py-3">0.264 US gal</td><td class="px-4 py-3">≈ 4 cups</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 ml</td><td class="px-4 py-3">0.034 fl oz</td><td class="px-4 py-3">≈ 1/5 teaspoon</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 US gallon</td><td class="px-4 py-3">3.785 litres</td><td class="px-4 py-3">UK gallon = 4.546 L</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3">1 US cup</td><td class="px-4 py-3">236.6 ml</td><td class="px-4 py-3">≈ 240 ml (rounded)</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Volume is where the two systems diverge most confusingly — a UK pint (568 ml) is larger than a US pint (473 ml), and recipes from different countries use different cup sizes. Our <a href="/convert/volume" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 hover:underline font-medium">Volume Converter</a> and <a href="/convert/cooking" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 hover:underline font-medium">Cooking Converter</a> eliminate the guesswork.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Temperature Conversions</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">0°C</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">= 32°F (freezing)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">37°C</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">= 98.6°F (body)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">100°C</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">= 212°F (boiling)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">The formula is °F = (°C × 9/5) + 32, but for quick mental estimates: double the Celsius value and add 30. That gives you a rough Fahrenheit within a few degrees. For exact results, use our <a href="/convert/temperature" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 hover:underline font-medium">Temperature Converter</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">All 25 Converters in One Place</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Beyond the everyday conversions listed above, our <a href="/convert" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 hover:underline font-medium">full converter directory</a> includes specialist converters for pressure, energy, power, frequency, angle, data storage, fuel economy, precious metals, shoe sizes, clothing sizes, running pace, cycling speed, number bases, Roman numerals, and more. Each converter is free, instant, and works on any device without sign-up.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">✓ Remember</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">All conversions happen <span class="text-white font-medium">locally in your browser</span> — your data never leaves your device. No server processing, no tracking, no accounts.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/why-world-uses-different-units/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 hover:border-amber-300 dark:hover:border-amber-700 hover:bg-amber-50/50 dark:hover:bg-amber-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-amber-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 group-hover:text-amber-600 dark:group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors">Why the World Uses Different Units</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/how-to-convert-kg-to-lbs/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 hover:border-amber-300 dark:hover:border-amber-700 hover:bg-amber-50/50 dark:hover:bg-amber-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-amber-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 group-hover:text-amber-600 dark:group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors">How to Convert KG to LBS</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/how-to-convert-celsius-to-fahrenheit/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 hover:border-amber-300 dark:hover:border-amber-700 hover:bg-amber-50/50 dark:hover:bg-amber-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-amber-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 group-hover:text-amber-600 dark:group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors">How to Convert Celsius to Fahrenheit</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-50 to-orange-50 dark:from-amber-900/20 dark:to-orange-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our 25 free unit converters</p>
          <a href="/convert" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Converters →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
